    <!-- SECTION 1: HERO WITH ORIGINAL POSTER ARTWORK INTEGRATION -->
    <header class="hero">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="hero-grid">
                <div class="hero-content">
                    <span class="section-label">A Raw Crime Syndicate Novel</span>
                    <h1 class="hero-title">The Blade <span>Code</span></h1>
                    <div class="hero-author">By Deva Harsha V</div>
                    <div class="hero-tagline">"When loyalty is sharpened, it becomes the deadliest blade of all."</div>
                    <p class="hero-hook">
                        In the scorched, unforgiving badlands of Kadapa, survival isn't a given—it's forged[cite: 1]. Follow three childhood friends as they transition from defiant street rebels to the rulers of an underground vigilante empire[cite: 1], challenging corruption and writing their own brutal code of justice in blood.
                    </p>
                </div>
                <div class="book-cover-container">
                    <!-- REPLACED GENERIC MOCKUP WITH THE PROVIDED POSTER LINK AS REQUESTED -->
                    <img src="https://cdn-gcs.inkitt.com/vertical_storycovers/506ff4d27d41ac89999fdb7bcf735847.jpg" alt="The Blade Code Poster Art" class="book-poster">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <a href="#story" class="scroll-indicator">
            <span>Explore The Code</span>
            <div class="scroll-mouse"><div class="scroll-wheel"></div></div>
        </a>
    </header>

    <!-- SECTION 2: STORY -->
    <section id="story" class="story-section">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label">The Synopsis</span>
            <h2 class="section-title">The Heart of Seema</h2>
            <div class="story-grid">
                <div class="story-left">
                    <blockquote class="story-highlight-quote">
                        "The world wasn't fair. The law wasn't equal. Strength decided truth."[cite: 1]
                    </blockquote>
                    <div class="story-summary">
                        <p>
                            Set in the rugged, dust-choked territory of Kadapa, <em>The Blade Code</em> tracks the gritty evolution of Ravi, Suri, and Imtiyaz[cite: 1]. Branded as the "Three Little Devils" during their chaotic youth, the trio learns early that the institutional systems of law and protection are designed to look away from the helpless[cite: 1].
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            As decades pass, their localized acts of street defiance crystallize into a sophisticated shadow empire known as the <strong>Seema Syndicate</strong>. Operating out of an abandoned rice mill with ironclad rules against harming women, children, or dealing drugs, they become an underground force of absolute vigilante justice.
                        </p>
                        <p>
                            Our protagonists face a relentless cascade of turf wars with invading gangs in a flaming movie theater and high-stakes tactical friction against the calculated state authorities led by DGP Varadaraj. It is a cinematic saga examining whether true justice can ever be achieved when born from complete lawlessness.
                        </p>
                    </div>
                    <div class="themes-container">
                        <h4 class="themes-title">Core Narrative Themes</h4>
                        <div class="theme-tags">
                            <span class="theme-tag">Unwavering Loyalty</span>
                            <span class="theme-tag">Vigilante Justice</span>
                            <span class="theme-tag">Street Authority</span>
                            <span class="theme-tag">Systems of Corruption</span>
                            <span class="theme-tag">The Cost of Brotherhood</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="stats-grid">
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <div class="stat-number">15</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Chapters</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <div class="stat-number">3</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Protagonists</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <div class="stat-number">10+</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Years Timespan</div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="stat-card">
                        <div class="stat-number">Action</div>
                        <div class="stat-label">Genre Theme</div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 3: CHARACTERS -->
    <section id="characters" class="characters-section">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label">The Pillars of The Syndicate</span>
            <h2 class="section-title">Main & Supporting Cast</h2>
            <div class="characters-grid">
                <!-- Ravi -->
                <div class="character-card">
                    <div class="character-body">
                        <h3 class="character-name">Ravi</h3>
                        <div class="character-role">The Strategic Leader</div>
                        <p class="character-desc">
                            The natural alpha and ideological anchor of the trio[cite: 1]. Having grown up watching his mother bow to oppressive village employers, something deep inside him permanently broke[cite: 1]. He possesses an instinctive ability to read human intent, command rooms without raising his voice, and design long-term survival frameworks for those beneath him[cite: 1].
                        </p>
                        <div class="character-traits">
                            <span class="trait-tag">Fearless</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Commanding</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Unbending</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Suri -->
                <div class="character-card">
                    <div class="character-body">
                        <h3 class="character-name">Suri</h3>
                        <div class="character-role">The Enforcer</div>
                        <p class="character-desc">
                            Quiet, observant, and lethal[cite: 1]. Suri acts as a silent shadow behind Ravi's visionary leadership[cite: 1]. He views violence not as an emotional outlet, but as a precise, mathematical language necessary to prevent complete structural chaos. His weapon of choice, a heavy sickle, is treated as an organic extension of his arm[cite: 1].
                        </p>
                        <div class="character-traits">
                            <span class="trait-tag">Silent</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Calculated</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Unstoppable</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Imtiyaz -->
                <div class="character-card">
                    <div class="character-body">
                        <h3 class="character-name">Imtiyaz</h3>
                        <div class="character-role">The Bridge & Negotiator</div>
                        <p class="character-desc">
                            The charismatic pulse of the brothers[cite: 1]. Raised fixing machinery at a local bus-stand puncture shop, he can pick locks, read complex tactical exits, and talk his way out of escalating bloodbaths[cite: 1]. While known for maintaining a sharp, confident smile even under gunfire, his fury is catastrophic when those he protects are targeted[cite: 1].
                        </p>
                        <div class="character-traits">
                            <span class="trait-tag">Charismatic</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Resourceful</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Vicious</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Varadaraj -->
                <div class="character-card">
                    <div class="character-body">
                        <h3 class="character-name">DGP Varadaraj</h3>
                        <div class="character-role">The Modern Antagonist</div>
                        <p class="character-desc">
                            A highly disciplined, cold, and intellectual Director General of Police operating out of Hyderabad. Unlike common corrupt local entities, Varadaraj respects the syndicate's tactical efficiency but views them as a profound threat to institutional dominance. He relies heavily on intelligence, psychological leveraging, and shadow extraction operations.
                        </p>
                        <div class="character-traits">
                            <span class="trait-tag">Analytical</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Ruthless</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Cold</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Anaya -->
                <div class="character-card">
                    <div class="character-body">
                        <h3 class="character-name">Anaya</h3>
                        <div class="character-role">The Truth Seeker</div>
                        <p class="character-desc">
                            An independent investigative journalist entering Kadapa with an outsider's sharp accent and clinical precision. She acts as a fierce philosophical counter-weight to Imtiyaz, continuously arguing that structural violence merely replaces one terror layout with another, challenging the very ethics of the syndicate's bloody code.
                        </p>
                        <div class="character-traits">
                            <span class="trait-tag">Idealistic</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Persistent</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Candid</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Ramesh -->
                <div class="character-card">
                    <div class="character-body">
                        <h3 class="character-name">Ramesh</h3>
                        <div class="character-role">The Catalyst of Betrayal</div>
                        <p class="character-desc">
                            A small-time street fixer previously shown mercy by the Seema Syndicate. Desperate, fragile, and easily compromised by cash injections, he agrees to serve as an informational proxy for external police agencies, proving Ravi’s thesis that true ruin always spawns from within the system rather than open warfare.
                        </p>
                        <div class="character-traits">
                            <span class="trait-tag">Fragile</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Volatile</span>
                            <span class="trait-tag">Compromised</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 4: CHAPTERS -->
    <section id="chapters" class="chapters-section">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label">The Chronicles</span>
            <h2 class="section-title">Chapter Directory</h2>
            <div class="chapters-grid">
                <!-- Ch 1 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 1</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Three Little Devils</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">In the searing heat of Kadapa, three reckless boys discover that rules are luxury commodities[cite: 1]. The local streets offer them an explicit alternative education in power and early consequence[cite: 1].</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 2 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 2</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Rise of the Seema Syndicate</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">A decade passes, morphing three defiant adolescents into legendary underworld enigmas. An abandoned rice mill transforms into the operational command center of a calculated shadow law.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 3 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 3</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Blades Before Law</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">When a local politician's son weaponizes institutional privilege to bury a horrific crime, Ravi and his brothers step in to prove that blind systems still possess a sharp, physical reckoning.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 4 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 4</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Lions of the Streets</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">An aggressive outside criminal element moves in to exploit the market networks. The resulting escalation sparks an chaotic, public warpath through screaming street blocks and passing freight trains.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 5 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 5</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Tea, Chains & Scars</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">Midnight reflection on the mill roof brings a heavy revelation. As the group defines their long-term vision, an unexpected warning transmission hints at a devastating leak inside their territory.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 6 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 6</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Love Is a Distraction</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">An investigative journalist named Anaya begins tracing the syndicate's operational history. Her pursuit introduces a volatile ideological friction that threatens the brothers' protective security perimeter.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 7 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 7</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Fire in the Theatre</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">Lured into a compromised parley inside the historic Surya Talkies cinema, the brothers find themselves outnumbered. They must cut through an engineered trap as the building is consumed by flames.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 8 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 8</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">One, Two, Three... Blood</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">Sheltering under a desolate urban flyover, a severely wounded crew updates their original blood covenant. They choose to strip away all internal boundaries to brace for absolute structural war.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 9 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 9</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Branded as Monsters</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">The state media machine warps the recent theater conflict into sensationalized public terror. In the distance, high-ranking state intelligence mastermind DGP Varadaraj assumes absolute control of the hunt.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 10 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 10</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">The MLA's Funeral March</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">An elite public execution is deliberately staged on the guest-house steps to frame the Syndicate. State enforcement units descend upon Kadapa, turning the region into a militarized legal net.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 11 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 11</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Love Turns Red</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">Anaya vanishes into thin air, exposing a calculated play executed via a compromised local informant. Imtiyaz is forced to abandon his trademark smile to deliver an uncompromising lecture on consequence.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 12 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 12</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Brothers Don't Break</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">An ambush in the suffocating humidity of the old textile warehouses leaves Suri grievously wounded. The violent response from the remaining brothers proves their internal bonds cannot be shattered.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 13 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 13</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">A Town That Fought Back</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">Heavy tactical reinforcement fleets roll into the village lines for a final clearance operation. In a stunning turning point, the marginalized local working population chooses to pick up tools and form a human wall.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 14 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 14</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Ghosts of Seema</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">Muthyala Center is professionally cleared of all public eyes for an engineered, final showdown. The shadow forces of Varadaraj collide directly with three men who have nothing left to lose.</p>
                </div>
                <!-- Ch 15 -->
                <div class="chapter-card">
                    <span class="chapter-num">Chapter 15</span>
                    <h3 class="chapter-title">Not Men - Legends</h3>
                    <p class="chapter-teaser">The aftermath of the battle leaves a permanent imprint. The brothers vanish completely into the fog of local folklore, leaving behind a persistent code that continues to guard the valleys.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 5: QUOTES -->
    <section id="quotes" class="quotes-section">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label">The Oral Lore</span>
            <h2 class="section-title">Words Forged in Iron</h2>
            
            <div class="featured-quote-container">
                <div class="featured-quote">"Violence stopped being an accident. It became a language."[cite: 1]</div>
                <div class="featured-quote-author">— The Evolution of the Three Devils</div>
            </div>

            <div class="quotes-grid">
                <div class="quote-card">
                    <p class="quote-text">"Real men carry steel... Real men don't cut their own fingers."[cite: 1]</p>
                    <span class="quote-context">Ravi & Imtiyaz, Age 12</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-card">
                    <p class="quote-text">"Because when people believe in you, they expect you to win every time... Then they'll learn that we're not gods."</p>
                    <span class="quote-context">Ravi, Rice Mill Terrace Dialogue</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-card">
                    <p class="quote-text">"Dreams make noise. Noise attracts knives. Then we sharpen ours."</p>
                    <span class="quote-context">Suri & Ravi, Preparing for Turf Warfare</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-card">
                    <p class="quote-text">"When the law chose blindness—blades chose justice."</p>
                    <span class="quote-context">The Creed of the Syndicate, Chapter 3</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-card">
                    <p class="quote-text">"You mistake fear for loyalty. Fear scatters... If they want demons, we decide the rules of hell."</p>
                    <span class="quote-context">DGP Varadaraj & Ravi, The Phone Transmission</span>
                </div>
                <div class="quote-card">
                    <p class="quote-text">"Everything looks important after it's done its work."</p>
                    <span class="quote-context">The Chai Shop Owner, Epilogue</span>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 6: JOURNEY / TIMELINE -->
    <section id="journey" class="journey-section">
        <div class="container">
            <span class="section-label">Chronological Narrative Arc</span>
            <h2 class="section-title">The Evolution Timeline</h2>

            <div class="timeline">
                <!-- Stage 1 -->
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">The Genesis</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">The Three Little Devils</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">Twelve-year-old outcasts skip school to master the laws of street consequence across abandoned quarries and train lines, carrying a single rusted butcher blade[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Stage 2 -->
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">The Shift</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">The First Drop of Blood</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">A violent defense of family honor near the fish market introduces the boys to coordinated tactical response[cite: 1]. Street interactions transform from play into calculated authority[cite: 1].</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Stage 3 -->
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">Institutional Failure</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">Blades Overwrite The Code</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">The formal legal network intentionally shields a high-profile criminal asset. The newly initialized Seema Syndicate steps into the void to deliver definitive, parallel justice.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Stage 4 -->
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">The Crisis Point</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">Surya Talkies In Flames</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">An existential betrayal traps the team inside a burning theater surrounded by execution crews. The brothers survive through sheer coordinated tactical brutality, but the state declares open war.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Stage 5 -->
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">The Collective Stand</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">The Defiance of Seema</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">Militarized state assets attempt a total sweeping raid of the region. The long-protected working class population rebels en masse, choosing to pick up blades alongside the syndicate.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <!-- Stage 6 -->
                <div class="timeline-item">
                    <div class="timeline-dot"></div>
                    <div class="timeline-content">
                        <span class="timeline-stage">The Resolution</span>
                        <h3 class="timeline-title">The Ghosts of Muthyala Center</h3>
                        <p class="timeline-desc">A pitch-black showdown eliminates institutional orchestrators. With their architectural objective realized, the brothers dissolve into the local scenery, leaving an immortal code behind.</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 7: ENDING -->
    <section class="ending-section">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="ending-container">
                <span class="section-label">The Final Page</span>
                <p class="ending-message">
                    The files vanished, the officers scattered, and the architectural structures of power systematically healed themselves by pretending the syndicate never breathed. But history cannot be scrubbed clean where blood has seeped into the asphalt. The brothers didn't exit as fallen martyrs or celebrated champions—they stepped aside as permanent structural reminders.
                </p>
                <div class="ending-quote-box">
                    <div class="ending-quote">"When law abandons people, people remember how to stand together."</div>
                </div>
                <div class="ending-reflection">
                    Because men can be tracked, broken, and systematically erased from records. But a code? Codes don't die. They simply wait.
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SECTION 8: FOOTER -->
    <footer class="footer">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="footer-title">THE <span>BLADE CODE</span></div>
            <div class="footer-author">Deva Harsha V — © 2026</div>
            <div class="footer-quote">"Loyalty, once sharpened, was the deadliest blade of all."[cite: 1]</div>
        </div>
    </footer>

    <!-- INTERACTIVE JAVASCRIPT FOR NAVIGATION -->
    <script>
        document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
            const sections = document.querySelectorAll('section');
            const navLinks = document.querySelectorAll('.nav-links a');

            window.addEventListener('scroll', () => {
                let current = '';
                sections.forEach(section => {
                    const sectionTop = section.offsetTop;
                    const sectionHeight = section.clientHeight;
                    if (pageYOffset >= (sectionTop - 200)) {
                        current = section.getAttribute('id');
                    }
                });

                navLinks.forEach(link => {
                    link.classList.remove('active');
                    if (link.getAttribute('href').slice(1) === current) {
                        link.classList.add('active');
                    }
                });
            });
        });
    </script>
<%- include('partials/footer') %>